In the context of your analogy, it means we look strictly at the edges where two photos overlap.

31:12.380 --> 31:23.580
If the pixel representing a rock on the right edge of photo A flawlessly matches the pixel of the exact same rock on the left edge of photo B, the cohomology condition is satisfied.

31:23.580 --> 31:24.140
Oh.

