38:53.420 --> 38:58.260
What is the difference between a normal probability and a unistochastic one?

38:58.260 --> 39:06.360
Well, in classical probability, like rolling a six-sided die, you have positive numbers that add up to 100%.

39:06.360 --> 39:10.380
A one-in-six chance is roughly 16.6%.

39:10.380 --> 39:10.620
Right.

39:10.840 --> 39:12.360
Simple positive percentages.

39:12.620 --> 39:15.860
