46:04.660 --> 46:12.680
If I measure the apparent length of that yardstick strictly across my flat 2D visual plane, it appears shorter.

46:12.980 --> 46:13.660
Yeah, perspective.

46:14.260 --> 46:15.520
The wood did not compress.

46:16.180 --> 46:22.600
Its geometric projection onto my specific visual plane changed because of the rotation.

46:22.780 --> 46:23.060
Right.

46:23.060 --> 46:28.220
If I try to carry a ladder horizontally through a narrow doorway, it won't fit.

46:28.220 --> 46:37.140
But if I angle the ladder, the projection of the ladder against the doorway is shorter and I can walk through, the ladder didn't shrink.

46:37.140 --> 46:47.220
In relativity, you can rotate an object, but instead of rotating it through spatial dimensions, a moving observer is rotating it through time.

46:47.420 --> 46:47.820
Wow.

46:47.820 --> 46:56.260
